{{Politics of Burkina Faso}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Burkina Faso]] on 9 June 1991. It followed a military coup in 1980, and would restore multi-party democracy. The new [[Constitution of Burkina Faso|constitution]] retained the [[presidential system]] of government, created a [[bicameralism|bicameral]] parliament, and limited the President to two seven-year terms. It was approved by 92.83% of voters with a 48.8% turnout.<ref name=AED>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/bf.html Elections in Burkina Faso] African Elections Database</ref>
