{{Refimprove|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox military unit |unit_name =Military Prosecution Service |native_name =Forsvarets Auditørkorps |image = [[File:Forsvarets Auditoerkorps.jpg|150px]] |caption =Coat of arms |dates ={{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1659}} |country = {{flag|Kingdom of Denmark}} |allegiance = |branch = [[Defence Command (Denmark)|Joined/shared]] |type = |role =[[Military justice]] |size =30<ref name=ForsvaretsAuditoerkorps>{{cite web|title=About |url=http://www.fmn.dk/videnom/Pages/ForsvaretsAuditoerkorpsopgaver.aspx |accessdate=1 December 2015 |language=Danish |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208093923/http://www.fmn.dk/videnom/Pages/ForsvaretsAuditoerkorpsopgaver.aspx |archivedate=8 December 2015 |df= }}</ref> |command_structure=[[Ministry of Defence (Denmark)|Ministry of Defence]] |garrison =[[Kastellet, Copenhagen|Kastellet]] |garrison_label =[[Headquarters]] |nickname =FAUK |patron = |motto = |colors = |colors_label = |march = |mascot = |equipment = |equipment_label = |battles = |anniversaries = |decorations = |battle_honours = |website ={{URL|http://www.fauk.dk/english/Pages/default.aspx|Official FAUK}} |disbanded = <!-- Commanders --> |commander1 =Lars Stevnsborg |commander1_label =[[Judge Advocate General]] |notable_commanders= <!-- Insignia --> |identification_symbol = |identification_symbol_label= }}
'''Military Prosecution Service''' or '''Judge Advocate General’s Corps''' ({{Lang-da|'''Forsvarets Auditørkorps'''}}, short '''''FAUK''''') is a Danish independent military [[prosecutor]] and the legal branch of the [[Danish military]]. It is a Level.I command and is under the [[Ministry of Defence (Denmark)|Ministry of Defence]]. The Judge Advocate General ({{lang-da|Generalauditør}}) heads the Defence Judge Advocate Corps. It is located at [[Kastellet, Copenhagen|Kastellet]] in [[Copenhagen]].
The Judge advocate General and [[Judge advocate]]s are members of the military system, but outside the military rank system. The [[Chief of Defence (Denmark)|Chief of Defence]], otherwise the commander of all Danish military personal, does not have authority over Judge advocates prosecutors.
In a military criminal case the Defence Judge Advocate Corps conducts investigation and decides whether or not a charge should be brought up.
