The '''European Patent Office Reports''' (EPOR) are a series of [[law report]]s, including decisions of the [[Boards of Appeal of the European Patent Office]]. The reports were published since 1979<ref> Sweet & Maxwell Ltd, [http://2.sweetandmaxwell.co.uk/docdel/abbrevs.cfm?letter=E ''ABBREVIATION and PRICE LIST FOR DOCDEL May 2007'']</ref> and since at least 1989 by [[Sweet & Maxwell]].<ref>[[United Kingdom Intellectual Property Office]], [http://www.ipo.gov.uk/practice-glossary.pdf ''Glossary of terms and abbreviations used in this Manual''] (Manual of Patent Practice). Consulted on March 1, 2008.</ref>

