The '''Ministry of Justice''' ({{lang-ur|{{nq|وزارت انصاف}}}}); abbreviated as '''MoJ''') is a [[Cabinet of Pakistan|Cabinet-level]] ministry of [[Government of Pakistan|Pakistan]], responsible and for the enforcement of law and [[administration of justice]].

The ministry's political executive figure is known as the [[Law_Minister_of_Pakistan|Minister for Law, Justice and Human Rights]], who must be an elected legislator and [[Parliament of Pakistan|Parliamentarian]]. The Minister for Justice is associated with enforcing laws and administration of government judicial departments, and is a public face of the government in legal services required by the state. The ministry's administration is headed by the [[Law Secretary of Pakistan]]. The ministry is also represented by the [[Attorney General of Pakistan|Attorney General]] as the chief law enforcement officer of the federal government, representing it in civilian [[Supreme Court of Pakistan|Supreme Court]] cases, and assisting the Minister for Justice and the government in legal cases. Both the Minister for Justice and Attorney General are nominated by the Prime Minister of Pakistan, and are members of the [[Cabinet of Pakistan|Cabinet]]. It is currently headed by [[ Farogh Naseem]] as of 20th August 2018.

